FIFA World Cup Group 3#Romania vs England|0\u20131]]''' || '''{{fb|ENG}}'''\n|-\n| 3 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|TCH}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 3#Czechoslovakia vs Brazil|1\u20134]]''' || '''{{fb|BRA|1968}}'''\n|-\n| 6 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|ROU|1965}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 3#Romania vs Czechoslovakia|2\u20131]]''' || '''{{fb|TCH}}'''\n|-\n| 7 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|ENG}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 3#England vs Brazil|0\u20131]]''' || '''{{fb|BRA|1968}}'''\n|-\n| 10 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|ROU|1965}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 3#Romania vs Brazil|2\u20133]]''' || '''{{fb|BRA|1968}}'''\n|-\n| 11 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|ENG}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 3#England vs Czechoslovakia|1\u20130]]''' || '''{{fb|TCH}}'''\n|}\n\n==== Group 4 ====\n{{main|1970 FIFA World Cup Group 4}}\n{{:1970 FIFA World Cup Group 4}}\n{| style=\"width:70%\" cellspacing=\"1\"\n|-\n!width=35%|\n!width=15%|\n!\n|-\n| 2 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|PER}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 4#Peru vs Bulgaria|3\u20132]]''' || '''{{fb|BUL|1967}}'''\n|-\n| 3 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|FRG}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 4#West Germany vs Morocco|2\u20131]]''' || '''{{fb|MAR}}'''\n|-\n| 6 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|PER}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 4#Peru vs Morocco|3\u20130]]''' || '''{{fb|MAR}}'''\n|-\n| 7 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|FRG}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 4#West Germany vs Bulgaria|5\u20132]]''' || '''{{fb|BUL|1967}}'''\n|-\n| 10 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|FRG}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 4#West Germany vs Peru|3\u20131]]''' || '''{{fb|PER}}'''\n|-\n| 11 June 1970\n|- style=font-size:90%\n| align=right|'''{{fb-rt|BUL|1967}}''' || align=center|'''[[1970 FIFA World Cup Group 4#Bulgaria vs Morocco|1\u20131]]''' || '''{{fb|MAR}}'''\n|}\n\n== Knockout stage ==\n{{main|1970 FIFA World Cup knockout stage}}\n\nThe eight teams that had advanced from the group stage entered a [[Single-elimination tournament|single-elimination]] style tournament, which also featured a third place play-off contested between the two losing semi-finalists. In this knockout stage (including the final), if a match was level at the end of 90 minutes, [[Extra time#Association football|extra time]] of two periods (15 minutes each) would be played. In matches prior to the final, if the score was still level after extra time then a coin toss by the referee would determine the winner. If the final was still level after 120 minutes' play then the match would instead be [[Replay (sports)|replayed]] at a later date.\n{{Round8 |widescore=yes\n<!-- Date-Place/Team 1/Score 1/Team 2/Score 2 -->\n<!-- quarter-finals -->\n|14 June \u2013 Mexico City|{{fb|URS|1955}}|0|'''{{fb|URU}}''' ([[Overtime (sports)#Association football|aet]])|'''1'''\n|14 June \u2013 Guadalajara|'''{{fb|BRA|1968}}'''|'''4'''|{{fb|PER}}|2\n|14 June \u2013 Toluca|'''{{fb|ITA}}'''|'''4'''|{{fb|MEX}}|1\n|14 June \u2013 Le\u00f3n|'''{{fb|FRG}}''' ([[Overtime (sports)#Association football|aet]])|'''3'''|{{fb|ENG}}|2\n<!-- semi-finals -->\n|17 June \u2013 Guadalajara|{{fb|URU}}|1|'''{{fb|BRA|1968}}'''|'''3'''\n|17 June \u2013 Mexico City|'''{{fb|ITA}}''' ([[Overtime (sports)#Association football|aet]])|'''4'''|{{fb|FRG}}|3\n<!-- final -->\n|21 June \u2013 Mexico City|'''{{fb|BRA|1968}}'''|'''4'''|{{fb|ITA}}|1\n<!-- third place -->\n|20 June \u2013 Mexico City|{{fb|URU}}|0|'''{{fb|FRG}}'''|'''1'''\n|consol=Third|3rdplace=yes\n}}\n\n''All times listed local ([[Central Time Zone|UTC\u22126]])''\n\n==== Quarter-finals ====\n{{football box\n|date=14 June 1970\n|time=12:00\n|team1={{fb-rt|URS|1955}}\n|score=[[1970 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Soviet Union vs Uruguay|0\u20131]]\n|aet=yes\n|report=[https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/worldcup/mexico1970/matches/round=251/match=1925/index.html Report]\n|team2={{fb|URU}}\n|goals2=[[V\u00edctor Esp\u00e1rrago|Esp\u00e1rrago]] {{goal|117}}\n|stadium=[[Estadio Azteca]], [[Mexico City]]\n|attendance=26,085\n|referee=[[Laurens van Ravens]] ([[Royal Dutch Football Association|Netherlands]])\n}}\n----\n{{football box\n|date=14 June 1970\n|time=12:00\n|team1={{fb-rt|ITA}}\n|score=[[1970 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Italy vs Mexico|4\u20131]]\n|report=[https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/worldcup/mexico1970/matches/round=251/match=1882/index.html Report]\n|team2={{fb|MEX}}\n|goals1=[[Javier Guzm\u00e1n|Guzm\u00e1n]] {{goal|25|o.g.}}<br />[[Luigi Riva|Riva]] {{goal|63||76}}<br />[[Gianni Rivera|Rivera]] {{goal|70}}\n|goals2=[[Jos\u00e9 Luis Gonz\u00e1lez D\u00e1vila|Gonz\u00e1lez]] {{goal|13}}\n|stadium=[[Estadio Nemesio D\u00edez|Estadio Luis Dosal]], [[Toluca]]\n|attendance=26,851\n|referee=[[Rudolf Scheurer]] ([[Swiss Football Association|Switzerland]])\n}}\n----\n{{football box\n|date=14 June 1970\n|time=12:00\n|team1={{fb-rt|BRA|1968}}\n|score=[[1970 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Brazil vs Peru|4\u20132]]\n|report=[https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/worldcup/mexico1970/matches/round=251/match=1768/index.html Report]\n|team2={{fb|PER}}\n|goals1=[[Roberto Rivellino|Rivellino]] {{goal|11}}<br />[[Tost\u00e3o]] {{goal|15||52}}<br />[[Jairzinho]] {{goal|75}}\n|goals2=[[Alberto Gallardo|Gallardo]] {{goal|28}}<br />[[Te\u00f3filo Cubillas|Cubillas]] {{goal|70}}\n|stadium=[[Estadio Jalisco]], [[Guadalajara]]\n|attendance=54,233\n|referee=[[Vital Loraux]] ([[Royal Belgian Football Association|Belgium]])\n}}\n----\n{{football box\n|date=14 June 1970\n|time=12:00\n|team1={{fb-rt|FRG}}\n|score=[[1970 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#West Germany vs England|3\u20132]]\n|aet=yes\n|report=[https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/worldcup/mexico1970/matches/round=251/match=1811/index.html Report]\n|team2={{fb|ENG}}\n|goals1=[[Franz Beckenbauer|Beckenbauer]] {{goal|68}}<br />[[Uwe Seeler|Seeler]] {{goal|82}}<br />[[Gerd M\u00fcller|M\u00fcller]] {{goal|108}}\n|goals2=[[Alan Mullery|Mullery]] {{goal|31}}<br />[[Martin Peters|Peters]] {{goal|49}}\n|stadium=[[Estadio Le\u00f3n|Estadio Nou Camp]], [[Le\u00f3n, Guanajuato|Le\u00f3n]]\n|attendance=23,357\n|referee=[[\u00c1ngel Norberto Coerezza]] ([[Argentine Football Association|Argentina]])\n}}\n\n==== Semi-finals ====\n{{football box\n|date=17 June 1970\n|time=16:00\n|team1={{fb-rt|URU}}\n|score=[[1970 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Uruguay vs Brazil|1\u20133]]\n|report=[https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/worldcup/mexico1970/matches/round=251/match=1771/index.html Report]\n|team2={{fb|BRA|1968}}\n|goals1=[[Luis Cubilla|Cubilla]] {{goal|19}}\n|goals2=[[Clodoaldo]] {{goal|44}}<br />[[Jairzinho]] {{goal|76}}<br />[[Roberto Rivellino|Rivellino]] {{goal|89}}\n|stadium=[[Estadio Jalisco]], [[Guadalajara]]\n|attendance=51,261\n|referee=[[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Ortiz de Mendibil]] ([[Royal Spanish Football Federation|Spain]])\n}}\n----\n{{main|Italy v West Germany (1970 FIFA World Cup)}}\n{{football box\n|date=17 June 1970\n|time=16:00\n|team1={{fb-rt|ITA}}\n|score=[[1970 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Italy vs West Germany|4\u20133]]\n|aet=yes\n|report=[https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=569/match=1838/classic-match/index.html Report]\n|team2={{fb|FRG}}\n|goals1=[[Roberto Boninsegna|Boninsegna]] {{goal|8}}<br />[[Tarcisio Burgnich|Burgnich]] {{goal|98}}<br />[[Luigi Riva|Riva]] {{goal|104}}<br />[[Gianni Rivera|Rivera]] {{goal|111}}\n|goals2=[[Karl-Heinz Schnellinger|Schnellinger]] {{goal|90}}<br />[[Gerd M\u00fcller|M\u00fcller]] {{goal|94||110}}\n|stadium=[[Estadio Azteca]], [[Mexico City]]\n|attendance=102,444\