{"title_page": "1970 FIFA World Cup Group 2", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n'''Group 2 of the [[1970 FIFA World Cup]]''' was contested in the [[Estadio Cuauht\u00e9moc]] and [[Estadio Nemesio D\u00edez]] between 2 and 11 June 1970. [[Italy national football team|Italy]] won the group, and advanced to the quarter-finals, along with [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]], who finished second by virtue of goal difference. [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] and [[Israel national football team|Israel]] failed to advance.\n\n==Standings==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|teamwidth=180\n\n|update=complete \n|winpoints=2\n|source=[https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/mexico1970/groups/index.html FIFA]\n\n|team1=ITA |team2=URU |team3=SWE |team4=ISR\n|result1=A |result2=A\n\n|win_ITA=1 |draw_ITA=2 |loss_ITA=0 |gf_ITA=1 |ga_ITA=0\n|win_URU=1 |draw_URU=1 |loss_URU=1 |gf_URU=2 |ga_URU=1\n|win_SWE=1 |draw_SWE=1 |loss_SWE=1 |gf_SWE=2 |ga_SWE=2\n|win_ISR=0 |draw_ISR=2 |loss_ISR=1 |gf_ISR=1 |ga_ISR=3\n\n|name_ITA={{fb|ITA|NATVAR=1946}}\n|name_ISR={{fb|ISR}}\n|name_URU={{fb|URU}}\n|name_SWE={{fb|SWE}}\n|res_col_header=Q\n|col_A=green1 |text_A=Advance to [[1970 FIFA World Cup#Knockout stage|knockout stage]]\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Matches==\nAll times local ([[Central Time Zone|UTC\u22126]])\n\n===Uruguay vs Israel===\n{{football box\n|date=2 June 1970\n|time=16:00\n|team1={{fb-rt|URU}}\n|score=2\u20130\n|report=[https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=250/match=1881/index.html Report]\n|team2={{fb|ISR}}\n|goals1=[[Ildo Maneiro|Maneiro]] {{goal|23}}<br />[[Juan Mujica|Mujica]] {{goal|50}}\n|stadium=[[Estadio Cuauht\u00e9moc]], [[Puebla, Puebla|Puebla]]\n|attendance=20,654\n|referee=[[Bobby Davidson]] ([[Scottish Football Association|Scotland]])\n}}\n{| width=92%\n|-\n|{{Football kit\n |pattern_la = _whiteborder\n |pattern_b  = _vneckwhite\n |pattern_ra = _whiteborder\n |pattern_sh = _shorts\n |pattern_so = _band_blue\n |leftarm    = 9